        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implement connection pooling and use asynchronous calls to minimize overhead. Profile your workload to identify bottlenecks, and consider caching frequent responses where applicable."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implementing Robust Error Handling and Monitoring"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Production systems must handle API failures gracefully. Define retry policies for transient errors (e.g., HTTP 429 or 5xx responses) and circuit breakers to prevent cascading failures. Integrate logging with tools like Prometheus or ELK stack to track API usage, latency percentiles, and error codes. Set up alerts for anomalies such as sudden spikes in failure rates or degraded performance, and maintain fallback mechanisms for critical paths."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Ensuring Security and Compliance in Production"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Secure the Ben2 inference API by enforcing strict access controls. Rotate API keys regularly and use short-lived tokens for sensitive operations. Enable TLS 1.3 for all communications and validate input data to prevent injection attacks. Implement rate limiting per client to avoid abuse, and audit logs for compliance with data protection regulations. For multi-tenant environments, isolate API usage with dedicated endpoints or namespaces."
          }
        ]
